Flex Box:
* Flexible Box
* One dimensional layout model

HTML Template:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Day 12 | Learn Flexbox, Grid</title>
</head>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
<body>
    <div class="main">
        <div class="item1">1</div>
        <div class="item2">2</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>


Container Property: 
display, flex-direction, flex-wrap, row-gap, column-gap,
justify-content, align-items, align-content.

Example:
display: flex;
flex-direction: column;
flex-wrap: wrap;
gap: 10px;
justify-content: center; -> main axis x
align-items: center; -> cross axis Y
align-content: center; -> cross axis Y
align-self: end;  -> cross axis Y

https://flexboxfroggy.com/

Flex-item Property:
Order, flex-grow, flex-basis, align-self.

.item1{
    flex-basis: 50%;
    background-color: aqua;
}

Grid: two dimensional

Container Property:
display: grid, grid-template-rows, column-gap, 

.main{
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 100px 100px;
    gap: 10px;
    justify-content: center;  -> main axis x
    align-content: center; -> cross axis Y
}

Grid Item Property:
grid-column, justify-items, align-items, justify-self, align-self.
